    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.31.17-18_0001" />
                <note type="curatorial">124-2       Aly Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">17</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                <hi rend="caps">UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA</hi>
                    <lb/>
                
                
                
                <hi rend="caps">COLLEGE OF ARTS AND SCIENCE</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">DEPARTMENT OF ENGLISH</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>Feb. 2,'61</dateline>	
                
                
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I really am a bit worried, but this is the "year of the Biography", and my faith in the Pattern is immense.</p>
                
                <p>I've just met my new classes &#8212; 190 or more <hi rend="underline">in Epic America</hi> (all very attentive) and eight in 
                    <hi rend="underline">Critical Essay</hi>. The eight are evidently the sort I want.</p>
                
                <p>Here is a confession: I just do <hi rend="underline">not</hi> know what you'ns there sent me as a birthday present! Isn't this ridiculous? Evidently things got mixed up. I do thank you just the same.</p>
                
                <p>And <hi rend="underline">did</hi> you write me since the Birthday Party,
                    
                    <note type="authorial">(over)</note>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.31.17-18_0002a"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">18</fw>
                    
                    since I sent the New York <hi rend="underline">letters</hi> to you? I've feared that mail may have been lost here. <hi rend="underline">Two</hi> expected letters have not turned up.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Anyway, 
                    the same affection always.</salute>
                
                <signed>John N.</signed>
                </closer>
                
                
            </div1>
            
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.31.17-18_0002b"/>
                
